        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">LowFruits specializes in one thing: finding keywords where weak or thin pages currently rank — indicating that a new or low-authority website could displace them with better content. For a new website with domain authority under 20, targeting keywords where DR 90 sites rank is a waste. LowFruits identifies the gaps — queries where forums, Reddit threads, or thin directories rank in positions 1–10 — and surfaces them as "low-hanging fruit" targets. This approach is the most effective strategy for new sites to get initial organic traffic.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Uniquely identifies keywords where weak pages rank — the best targets for new websites</h4><p>No other tool under $100 focuses specifically on finding keywords where the current top-10 results are beatable by a new site. This is the most actionable insight for low-authority domains.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>SERP weakness scoring — automatically grades how beatable each keyword's current results are</h4><p>Each keyword gets a "fruit score" showing how weak the current results are. Higher fruit score = easier target. No manual SERP analysis required.</p></div></li>
