  <!-- HOW WE TESTED -->
  <section class="problem-section">
    <div class="problem-header">
      <span class="label-pill">Buyer's guide</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">How to choose the right <span class="accent">SEO tools under $100.</span></h2>
      <p>The five questions that determine whether a cheap SEO tool is cheap and capable, or cheap and useless.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ba-grid">
      <div class="ba-col after" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Decide first: do you want to do SEO or have SEO done?</h4>
              <p>Every research tool under $100 (SE Ranking, Ubersuggest, Mangools) requires 20–40 hours/month of your time. theStacc at $99/month requires zero hours after setup. Different tools for different buyers. Know which you are before shopping.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Test the entry-level plan on your actual use case before subscribing</h4>
              <p>Most tools have feature gaps on the cheapest plan that only appear when you start using it. SE Ranking's 750-keyword limit is fine for 1–2 sites and hits fast for an agency. Mangools' daily search limits are fine for casual use and frustrating for heavy users. Test on your specific workflow.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">03</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Build your stack around one primary job, not one tool that does everything</h4>
              <p>The best under-$100 stacks pair tools by job: theStacc (content) + SE Ranking (research) + Seobility (audit). Each does one thing excellently. A tool that does everything under $100 does nothing excellently.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">04</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Calculate what your time is worth before choosing a DIY research tool</h4>
              <p>SE Ranking at $52/month is a great deal if you enjoy SEO and have 20–40 hours/month. At $30/hour, those hours are worth $600–1,200/month. theStacc at $99/month removes those hours entirely. The math often makes the more expensive tool cheaper.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">05</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Require meaningful trials before entering payment information</h4>
              <p>Seobility's free tier, Mangools' 10-day no-credit-card trial, and theStacc's $1 trial are the most honest offers on this list. Tools that require payment upfront for a "free" trial are harder to evaluate honestly. Prioritize tools you can test meaningfully before committing.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
